A Queensland teenager who stands accused of stabbing a classmate said that he was attempting to scare him into ending his bullying behaviour.

The 16-year-old said he wanted to 'jab' the other boy, and has pleaded guilty to unlawfully wounding, but maintains he is not guilty to the charge of attempted murder or wounding in an attempt to maim or disfigure.

The boy, who cannot be named, was 14 when he stabbed his fellow year ten student with a kitchen knife at a Brisbane school in August 2013.

