The accused said he panicked and raced off when the victim made a gargling sound, thinking he had caused serious injury.

He dialled triple-zero and said, 'I think I just killed someone.'

The court has previously heard the wound was more than 5cm deep, and that the teenager decided to stab his classmate in the neck because it had fat and 'nothing important'.

The accused agreed he had earlier told a friend he was going to kill the victim, but said had not meant it and was just 'venting anger'.

